Le Nguyen Hoang Yen is an Intern/Fresher AI/ML Engineer with no commercial experience, focusing on Artificial Intelligence, Machine Learning, and Deep Learning. Their core expertise spans Computer Vision, Data Analysis, Optimization, and Algorithms, with practical application in Transformer-based architectures. Academic projects include developing and analyzing algorithms for Top-K high-utility itemset search in uncertain databases, implementing stock price prediction models leveraging optimization and deep learning techniques, and building a Transformer-based Optical Character Recognition (OCR) system for diverse document types, demonstrating hands-on experience with Scikit-learn, TensorFlow, and PyTorch.
Technically, Le Nguyen Hoang Yen is proficient in Python, Java, and C#. They possess hands-on experience with databases such as MySQL and SQL Server, and have exposure to containerization using Docker. Their development toolkit includes Google Colab and Kaggle for data science and machine learning workflows. Currently pursuing a Bachelor of Computer Science, they also hold certifications in Foundations of Usability Testing and Aptis Esol, reflecting an intermediate English proficiency and a foundational understanding of usability principles.